It became a division of the Cincinnati-based Federated Department Stores in 1994 (later renamed as Macy’s, Inc. in 2007), as a Bloomingdale’s department store chain affiliate. As of 2015, Macy’s was the largest U.S. department store company by retail sales. As of February 2019, there were 584 full-line stores with the Macy’s nameplate in operation throughout the United States, Puerto Rico, and Guam.
